Fixed: The Abaqus file format reader in GridIn::read_abaqus() got
itself into all sorts of troubles when reading files that had
DOS/Windows line endings, producing error messages that did not at all
help in diagnosing the underlying cause. This has now been fixed: The
reader can deal with such files without errors now.
